# Notion Itinerary WebApp Environment Variables Template

# Database Configuration (Choose one)

# Option 1: Supabase Database (Recommended)
# Get your project details from: https://app.supabase.com
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Option 2: Notion Integration (Legacy)
# Get your integration token from: https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
NOTION_API_KEY=your_notion_integration_token_here
VITE_NOTION_API_KEY=your_notion_integration_token_here

# Admin Panel (Required)
# Set a secure password for admin access
VITE_ADMIN_PASSWORD=your_secure_admin_password

# Image Service (Required)
# Get your API key from: https://www.pexels.com/api/
PEXELS_API_KEY=your_pexels_api_key_here
VITE_PEXELS_API_KEY=your_pexels_api_key_here

# AI Service Providers (At least one required)
# Choose one or more AI providers for content enhancement

# Google Gemini (Recommended)
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# OpenAI
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Anthropic Claude
CLAUDE_API_KEY=your_claude_api_key_here
VITE_CLAUDE_API_KEY=your_claude_api_key_here

# OpenRouter (Alternative AI provider)
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
VITE_OPENROUTER_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct:free

# AI Configuration (Optional)
# Set your preferred AI provider (gemini, openai, claude, openrouter)
VITE_AI_PROVIDER=gemini

# Development Configuration (Optional)
NODE_ENV=development

# Notes:
# - VITE_ prefixed variables are exposed to the frontend
# - Non-VITE_ prefixed variables are server-side only
# - For security, server-side functions should use non-VITE_ variables
# - Both versions are included for backward compatibility during transition
# - Remove VITE_ prefixed sensitive variables in production for better security

# Required Services Setup:

## For Supabase Database (Recommended):
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://app.supabase.com
# 2. Copy your project URL and anon key from Settings > API
# 3. Run the SQL schema provided in the setup documentation
# 4. Get Pexels API key for image search functionality
# 5. Choose at least one AI provider for content enhancement
# 6. Set a secure admin password for management features

## For Notion Database (Legacy):
# 1. Create a Notion integration at https://www.notion.so/my-integrations
# 2. Share your Notion database with the integration
# 3. Follow steps 4-6 above